The paper proposes a system architecture for enabling predictive query functionality in relational databases, with a focus on time series data. This work involves developing a prediction index that satisfies statistical accuracy, high throughput, low query latency, and flexibility across DB/machines. The paper also presents algorithmic contributions for incremental prediction and time-varying noise variance estimation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Database), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
